WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:06.310 --> 00:00:07.950
-The church counsel has
already discussed it.

00:00:07.950 --> 00:00:09.485
-I think to know and
this is going.

00:00:09.485 --> 00:00:11.780
-We've decided to offer the
position to Vi Rose Hill.

00:00:11.780 --> 00:00:13.160
-Thank you, Pastor.

00:00:13.160 --> 00:00:15.390
ANNOUNCER: They live in
the same small town.

00:00:15.390 --> 00:00:16.460
-People do care.

00:00:16.460 --> 00:00:19.455
And if don't like that maybe you
should move to New York.

00:00:19.455 --> 00:00:21.650
-I did not ask to be made
choir director.

00:00:21.650 --> 00:00:23.585
The council chose me over you.

00:00:23.585 --> 00:00:24.210
-Mm-hmm.

00:00:24.210 --> 00:00:26.540
ANNOUNCER: They share
the big dreams.

00:00:26.540 --> 00:00:29.765
-Today, we are gonna go out
there and we are gonna win

00:00:29.765 --> 00:00:31.015
this thing.

00:00:34.120 --> 00:00:36.125
Stop, stop, stop.

00:00:36.125 --> 00:00:37.017
Next year.

00:00:37.017 --> 00:00:37.730
-There's not gonna be a year.

00:00:37.730 --> 00:00:39.710
It's too expensive and
we always lose.

00:00:39.710 --> 00:00:42.185
ANNOUNCER: But the only way
to win the competition--

00:00:42.185 --> 00:00:43.130
-We gotta shake 'em up.

00:00:43.130 --> 00:00:44.980
-Pop, pop, pop.

00:00:44.980 --> 00:00:46.970
-Get your Beyonce
out of my face.

00:00:46.970 --> 00:00:49.480
ANNOUNCER: --is for someone
to change their tune.

00:00:49.480 --> 00:00:52.230
-(SINGING) Whoa!

00:00:52.230 --> 00:00:52.800
-Are you kidding me?

00:00:52.800 --> 00:00:54.680
Make some noise up in this--

00:00:54.680 --> 00:00:55.150
[GASPING]

00:00:55.150 --> 00:00:58.001
-Y'all remember my
grandson, Randy.

00:00:58.001 --> 00:00:58.887
-He's a good singer, Mama.

00:00:58.887 --> 00:01:00.570
-You just wanna be near
my little girl.

00:01:00.570 --> 00:01:04.285
[MUSIC - "MAYBE I'M AMAZED"]

00:01:04.285 --> 00:01:07.596
[MUSIC - "MAN IN THE MIRROR"]

00:01:07.596 --> 00:01:09.840
-He completely changed the
way the choir sings.

00:01:09.840 --> 00:01:10.990
Who knows what he'll do next?

00:01:10.990 --> 00:01:13.224
-I love those old songs
but Randy's right.

00:01:16.407 --> 00:01:17.580
-We are not going
on like this.

00:01:17.580 --> 00:01:19.620
Not you, not me, and
not this choir.

00:01:19.620 --> 00:01:21.000
-Well, I am who I am.

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:23.750
-Well, maybe you were
five procedures ago.

00:01:23.750 --> 00:01:25.890
And how much did she
spend on all that?

00:01:25.890 --> 00:01:28.888
-Who cares if I've had a few
little nips and tucks?

00:01:28.888 --> 00:01:31.450
God didn't make plastic surgeons
so they could starve.

00:01:31.450 --> 00:01:32.470
-That was amazing.

00:01:32.470 --> 00:01:34.720
-Singing is the only time
I feel important.

00:01:34.720 --> 00:01:35.870
-You know we're going
to LA, right?

00:01:35.870 --> 00:01:37.870
Someone could hear you who
might actually matter.

00:01:37.870 --> 00:01:39.880
-Baby, nobody ends up with
the boy they like

00:01:39.880 --> 00:01:41.299
when they were 16.

00:01:41.299 --> 00:01:42.096
-This isn't about that.

00:01:42.096 --> 00:01:43.590
This is about me.

00:01:43.590 --> 00:01:48.072
ANNOUNCER: Raise your
voice and dream big.

00:01:48.072 --> 00:01:50.580
[MUSIC - "JOYFUL NOISE"]

00:01:50.580 --> 00:01:52.960
-You are infallible,
untouchable, unlovable.

00:01:52.960 --> 00:01:56.470
Ow, you're breakin' my hair.

00:01:56.470 --> 00:01:57.720
-Put that online.

00:02:02.050 --> 00:02:04.610
-We just go to Los Angeles
and we do our best.

00:02:09.790 --> 00:02:10.940
-Don't look at my butt.

00:02:10.940 --> 00:02:13.614
I'm a good girl.

00:02:13.614 --> 00:02:16.094
Stop.

00:02:16.094 --> 00:02:18.410
-I'm very, very proud
to be your mother.

00:02:18.410 --> 00:02:20.825
I love you.

00:02:20.825 --> 00:02:22.250
ANNOUNCER: Joyful Noise.

00:02:26.525 --> 00:02:28.740
-Quit it with those nails,
Edward Scissorhand.

